00:15:12,512 --> 00:15:15,412
He seems to have run into old acquaintance yesterday

274
00:15:15,412 --> 00:15:19,712
and went out to see that person.

275
00:15:19,712 --> 00:15:21,712
If that's case...

276
00:15:31,212 --> 00:15:34,512
I got it. So, that's how it was.

277
00:15:34,512 --> 00:15:38,212
Honda, what went on between you and Ogata?

278
00:15:38,212 --> 00:15:39,312
I've been trying to tell you.

279
00:15:39,312 --> 00:15:41,612
I don't know what on earth is going on.

280
00:15:48,812 --> 00:15:51,312
Where am I?

281
00:15:51,312 --> 00:15:56,712
It seems that I had it out with someone over there.

282
00:15:59,912 --> 00:16:05,512
I... I pushed him down from here?

283
00:16:05,512 --> 00:16:08,512
I was afraid of getting caught.

284
00:16:08,512 --> 00:16:12,012
But I had a headache and felt faint.

285
00:16:12,012 --> 00:16:14,212
I figured out that I should hide myself.

286
00:16:15,912 --> 00:16:19,612
When I finally thought that I could somehow manage to move...

287
00:16:22,012 --> 00:16:26,312
"Out of order" -No clue on the roof.

288
00:16:26,312 --> 00:16:28,212
Is there anyone here?

289
00:16:28,212 --> 00:16:29,812
This is the police.

290
00:16:29,812 --> 00:16:32,312
Police?

291
00:16:32,312 --> 00:16:34,412
I didn't want to get caught.

292
00:16:35,612 --> 00:16:39,612
But why did I try to kill him to begin with?

293
00:16:39,612 --> 00:16:41,412
If he doesn't know,

294
00:16:41,412 --> 00:16:44,112
there's no way anyone else would know.

295
00:16:44,112 --> 00:16:47,412
So, there's no other way than for a detective to solve it for him.

296
00:16:49,212 --> 00:16:52,312
Why did I try to kill that man?

297
00:16:52,312 --> 00:16:54,012
You're wrong, Mr. Honda.

298
00:16:55,012 --> 00:16:58,012
Didn't you come to visit Masaaki Ogata

299
00:16:58,012 --> 00:17:00,812
because he was an old acquaintance of yours?

300
00:17:00,812 --> 00:17:02,912
Old acquaintance?

301
00:17:02,912 --> 00:17:04,212
Officer Takagi,

302
00:17:04,212 --> 00:17:08,612
I think that Masaaki Ogata had a hoarse voice.

303
00:17:08,612 --> 00:17:10,812
Yes, a very gruff one.

304
00:17:10,812 --> 00:17:13,512
Can't you remember, Mr. Honda?

305
00:17:13,512 --> 00:17:15,212
It's the man with a hoarse voice.

306
00:17:15,212 --> 00:17:19,212
You became acquainted with that man eight years ago at a pub.

307
00:17:20,812 --> 00:17:22,312
It couldn't be.

308
00:17:22,312 --> 00:17:24,012
Eight years ago,

309
00:17:24,012 --> 00:17:26,112
a man with a hoarse voice.

310
00:17:26,112 --> 00:17:28,612
I got to know him at a pub.

311
00:17:28,612 --> 00:17:32,212
A man with a hoarse voice...

312
00:17:32,212 --> 00:17:33,812
It's him!

313
00:17:33,812 --> 00:17:36,012
He looked completely different,

314
00:17:36,012 --> 00:17:38,012
but his voice...

315
00:17:39,712 --> 00:17:43,812
I'll collect the money from you even I have to go to hell!

316
00:17:43,812 --> 00:17:45,812
You get that?

317
00:17:46,812 --> 00:17:48,612
What's with you?

318
00:17:51,412 --> 00:17:53,512
It's you after all.

319
00:17:56,212 --> 00:17:58,612
It's true it's been eight years ago,

320
00:17:58,612 --> 00:18:01,112
but the statute of limitations hasn't run out yet.

321
00:18:01,112 --> 00:18:03,112
So you're telling me to turn myself in?

322
00:18:03,112 --> 00:18:04,612
If you pay for your sins,

323
00:18:04,612 --> 00:18:06,112
you can live your life under the sun

324
00:18:06,112 --> 00:18:08,812
without feeling guilty towards anyone, right?

325
00:18:13,212 --> 00:18:16,312
I was somehow trying to get him to turn himself in.

326
00:18:16,312 --> 00:18:18,412
He's a good person after all, isn't he?

327
00:18:18,412 --> 00:18:19,412
But...

328
00:18:19,412 --> 00:18:21,012
That good man ended up...

329
00:18:21,012 --> 00:18:24,412
So how'd you end up killing Ogata, then?

330
00:18:24,412 --> 00:18:26,512
I don't remember that part.

331
00:18:26,512 --> 00:18:28,712
It's the other way around.

332
00:18:28,712 --> 00:18:32,512
Since you knew the wrongdoings of the past,

333
00:18:32,512 --> 00:18:34,812
Masaaki Ogata tried to get rid of you.

334
00:18:34,812 --> 00:18:36,012
After killing you,

335
00:18:36,012 --> 00:18:38,312
he was probably planning to take your body to the remote mountains

336
00:18:38,312 --> 00:18:39,912
to bury and hide it.

337
00:18:39,912 --> 00:18:41,512
After making preparations to do so,

338
00:18:41,512 --> 00:18:43,812
he called you over to come to your office that was empty

339
00:18:43,812 --> 00:18:45,412
because it was a holiday.

340
00:18:45,412 --> 00:18:47,912
Ogata carried out his scheme.

341
00:18:51,412 --> 00:18:53,812
But he failed to kill you.

342
00:18:53,812 --> 00:18:56,812
So he ended up pushing you off the roof.

343
00:19:01,312 --> 00:19:03,312
Which means that when we saw it...

344
00:19:03,312 --> 00:19:05,012
The one who was pushed down...

345
00:19:05,012 --> 00:19:06,712
Was Mr. Honda?

346
00:19:06,712 --> 00:19:11,612
Then Mr. Honda, who Ogata was ready to finish off

347
00:19:11,612 --> 00:19:14,112
was dragged back into the office.

348
00:19:14,112 --> 00:19:18,412
As proof of this... See? His jacket is soiled.

349
00:19:18,412 --> 00:19:20,712
But the one who fell to the ground

350
00:19:20,712 --> 00:19:22,812
was the one called Ogata.

351
00:19:22,812 --> 00:19:24,212
Exactly.

352
00:19:24,212 --> 00:19:25,812
However back then,

353
00:19:25,812 --> 00:19:27,912
Mr. Honda had incurred a severe blow to his head

354
00:19:27,912 --> 00:19:31,712
that was bad enough to cause amnesia and passed out.

355
00:19:31,712 --> 00:19:34,012
So he couldn't have pushed Masaaki Ogata down.

356
00:19:34,012 --> 00:19:37,312
If so, there's only one plausible explanation.

357
00:19:37,312 --> 00:19:40,112
Masaaki Ogata, after finishing his target off,

358
00:19:40,112 --> 00:19:44,112
was scheming to bury and hide him as planned.

359
00:19:44,112 --> 00:19:45,312
In order to do so,

360
00:19:45,312 --> 00:19:49,312
he had to hide traces of Mr. Honda coming over.

361
00:19:53,212 --> 00:19:56,712
I've got to get rid of that too.

362
00:19:56,712 --> 00:19:58,712
Where's his glasses?

363
00:19:58,712 --> 00:20:00,012
Are they here?

364
00:20:03,412 --> 00:20:04,612
There it is.

365
00:20:05,912 --> 00:20:08,412
However, he was leaning on a really slippery surface.

366
00:20:08,412 --> 00:20:10,912
Back then... Remember?

367
00:20:19,212 --> 00:20:23,412
In other words, it was not that one person was pushed off twice,

368
00:20:23,412 --> 00:20:26,712
but two people switched places partway

369
00:20:26,712 --> 00:20:29,712
in a matter of 10 minutes.

370
00:20:29,712 --> 00:20:33,712
So that's the truth behind the long fall.

371
00:20:39,012 --> 00:20:40,812
What a bummer.

372
00:20:44,112 --> 00:20:45,612
Honda.

373
00:20:45,612 --> 00:20:49,612
It may be true that you did nothing

374
00:20:49,612 --> 00:20:52,412
as far as Masaaki Ogata is concerned.

375
00:20:52,412 --> 00:20:55,812
But you attacked and went as far as to confine Officer Chiba.

376
00:20:55,812 --> 00:20:57,112
But Inspector...

377
00:20:57,112 --> 00:20:59,012
That's a fact.

378
00:20:59,012 --> 00:21:01,012
Inspector.

379
00:21:01,012 --> 00:21:03,012
You'll have to come with me.

380
00:21:03,012 --> 00:21:04,112
Yes, sir.

381
00:21:04,112 --> 00:21:06,012
I feel sorry for him.

382
00:21:06,012 --> 00:21:08,112
-Yeah. -Yeah.

383
00:21:08,112 --> 00:21:09,412
Conan.

384
00:21:09,412 --> 00:21:13,112
There's nothing I can do about it.

385
00:21:13,112 --> 00:21:16,112
He may have panicked after losing his memory,

386
00:21:16,112 --> 00:21:18,812
but he did what he did and that's fact.

387
00:21:18,812 --> 00:21:20,412
Besides,

388
00:21:20,412 --> 00:21:24,012
I think he understands more than anyone else does.

389
00:21:24,012 --> 00:21:26,912
I'm sorry for troubling you.

390
00:21:26,912 --> 00:21:28,312
Not at all.

391
00:21:29,512 --> 00:21:31,112
Never mind the handcuffs.

392
00:21:31,112 --> 00:21:32,912
I'm asking him to come along voluntarily.

393
00:21:32,912 --> 00:21:36,312
But before that, let's take you to the hospital.

394
00:21:36,312 --> 00:21:40,312
Let's have them treat your head wound, Mr. Honda.

395
00:21:40,912 --> 00:21:42,712
Masaaki Ogata was arrested

396
00:21:42,712 --> 00:21:44,712
under charges of the robbery that was committed eight years ago,

397
00:21:44,712 --> 00:21:48,712
as well as the attempted murder against Mr. Honda soon after the incident.

398
00:21:48,712 --> 00:21:51,112
Both of the charges were dropped shortly.

399
00:23:13,012 --> 00:23:17,312
Dr. Agasa, you really did a good job again this time too, didn't you?

400
00:23:17,312 --> 00:23:19,212
-For sure. -Yes.

401
00:23:19,212 --> 00:23:21,212
Well, I guess so.

402
00:23:23,812 --> 00:23:24,912
A rainbow.

403
00:23:26,712 --> 00:23:29,012
-Splendid. -It's pretty!

404
00:23:30,312 --> 00:23:32,412
I knew that things would turn out this way to begin with.

405
00:23:32,412 --> 00:23:34,712
That the incident would start at 2:00,

406
00:23:34,712 --> 00:23:36,012
that is, it would start out like the movie "The Double Hour"

407
00:23:36,012 --> 00:23:38,712
but end up happily like when one views a double rainbow.

408
00:23:38,712 --> 00:23:40,512
Another one of his puns.

409
00:23:40,512 --> 00:23:42,412
I went out of my way to compliment him.

410
00:23:42,412 --> 00:23:44,012
All down the drain.

411
00:23:45,212 --> 00:23:47,012
Another punch line with a long decent.

412
00:23:47,012 --> 00:23:48,812
What a far-fetched analogy.

413
00:23:48,812 --> 00:23:50,512
It's like always.

414
00:23:52,012 --> 00:23:53,812
"Next Episode" -What seems to be matter?

415
00:23:56,312 --> 00:23:59,112
That's the concept of the design plan

416
00:23:59,112 --> 00:24:01,412
that Mr. Murase showed to Mr. Inomata.

417
00:24:01,412 --> 00:24:02,912
I think it would be more accurate to say that

418
00:24:02,912 --> 00:24:06,012
this is not an accident, but rather a homicide.

419
00:24:06,012 --> 00:24:09,812
However, why was Mr. Inomata there?

420
00:24:09,812 --> 00:24:10,812
This is...

